        <article class="recipe" id="team-work">
          <h2 class="recipe__title">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M4 19.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 17H20"/><path d="M6.5 2H20v20H6.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 4 19.5v-15A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 2"/><line x1="8" y1="7" x2="16" y2="7"/><line x1="8" y1="11" x2="13" y2="11"/></svg>
            Team Work with Linear
          </h2>

          <!-- Introduction -->
          <section class="recipe-section" id="team-intro">
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Introduction</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">This recipe shows how to run OpenCastle in a team context with Linear as the canonical issue tracker. You’ll connect Linear, generate tracked issues from a PRD, partition work across convoy tasks, and run an agentic convoy that produces review-ready feature branches for each task.</p>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">Integrating Linear provides traceability and auditability — every generated commit maps to a Linear issue, agents update issue status automatically, and PRs reference the originating issues so work can be triaged and closed in a single workflow. This setup enables parallel development with clear ownership and automatic issue transitions when code lands.</p>
          </section>

          <!-- What you'll set up -->
          <section class="recipe-section" id="team-what-youll-build">
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">What you'll set up</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">A Linear → OpenCastle → Agents → PR workflow that keeps issues, tasks and code tightly coupled. The convoy will create branches for tasks, attach Linear issue IDs to commits, and update issue status as work progresses.</p>

            <div class="recipe-mockup">
              <div class="recipe-mockup__chrome">
                <div class="recipe-mockup__dots"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>
                <div class="recipe-mockup__url">Linear — Your Team</div>
              </div>
              <div class="recipe-mockup__body">
                <div class="mockup-section-label">Linear board</div>
                <div class="mockup-grid">
                  <div class="mockup-card mockup-card--text">
                    <div class="mockup-card__title">To Do</div>
                    <div class="mockup-card__text">PRJ-101 · Create login form</div>
                    <div class="mockup-card__text">PRJ-102 · Auth API</div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="mockup-card mockup-card--text">
                    <div class="mockup-card__title">In Progress</div>
                    <div class="mockup-card__text">PRJ-103 · Session management</div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="mockup-card mockup-card--text">
                    <div class="mockup-card__title">Done</div>
                    <div class="mockup-card__text">PRJ-100 · Design auth flow</div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="recipe-mockup__pages">
                <span class="recipe-mockup__page recipe-mockup__page--active">Linear</span>
                <span class="recipe-mockup__page">OpenCastle</span>
                <span class="recipe-mockup__page">Agents</span>
                <span class="recipe-mockup__page">PR</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <ul class="recipe-section__list">
              <li><strong>Connect Linear</strong> — grant an API key so OpenCastle can create and update issues.</li>
              <li><strong>Generate issues</strong> — create an epic and child issues from a PRD or by hand.</li>
              <li><strong>Partition code</strong> — map issue ownership to file globs so agents don't collide.</li>
              <li><strong>Run a convoy</strong> — agents produce branches and PR-ready changes that reference Linear issues.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <!-- Prerequisites -->
          <section class="recipe-section" id="team-prerequisites">
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Prerequisites</h3>
            <ul class="recipe-prereq">
              <li>Node.js 22 or later (required for built-in SQLite support)</li>
              <li>Git installed and available on your PATH</li>
              <li>An AI coding IDE — VS Code with GitHub Copilot, Cursor, or Claude Code</li>
              <li>A Linear workspace with at least one project</li>
              <li>A LINEAR_API_KEY (Settings → API → Personal API keys)</li>
              <li>A shared repository that your team has access to</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <!-- Step 1 -->
          <section class="recipe-section recipe-step" id="team-step-1">
            <div class="recipe-step__number">1</div>
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Step 1: Initialize</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">Initialize OpenCastle in your team repo. From your local clone, run the initializer and select the Linear team plugin when prompted.</p>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">Terminal</div>
              <pre><code>$ cd your-team-repo
$ npx opencastle init</code></pre>
            </div>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">Interactive prompts will ask you to:</p>
            <ul class="recipe-section__list">
              <li><strong>Select IDE</strong> — choose VS Code (with Copilot) or another supported editor.</li>
              <li><strong>Enable team tools</strong> — pick <strong>Linear</strong> so OpenCastle can create and update issues.</li>
              <li><strong>Install skills</strong> — accept defaults to write the skills and agent configs into <code>.github/</code>.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="recipe-output">
              <pre><code>  ✓ Detected: VS Code
  ✓ Writing .github/instructions/
  ✓ Writing .github/skills/
  ✓ Writing .github/agents/
  ✓ Linear plugin enabled
  ✓ OpenCastle initialized successfully</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> Keep your API keys ready — you'll need <code>LINEAR_API_KEY</code> later. Store keys in <code>.env</code> locally and use CI secrets for pipelines.</div>
          </section>

          <!-- Step 2 -->
          <section class="recipe-section recipe-step" id="team-step-2">
            <div class="recipe-step__number">2</div>
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Step 2: Connect Linear</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">Provide a Linear API key and verify connectivity with the doctor command. Use the long key format so the client can authenticate reliably.</p>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">Terminal</div>
              <pre><code>$ export LINEAR_API_KEY="lin_api_ABC123def456..."
$ npx opencastle doctor</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-output">
              <pre><code>  ✓ Env: LINEAR_API_KEY found
  ✓ Linear: reachable (workspace=Your Workspace)
  ✓ MCP server: configured
  ✓ All checks passed · doctor OK</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> Add the key to <code>.env</code> for local development and to your CI provider as a secret for pipeline runs. After updating secrets, restart your terminal or IDE to pick up the change.</div>
          </section>

          <!-- Step 3 -->
          <section class="recipe-section recipe-step" id="team-step-3">
            <div class="recipe-step__number">3</div>
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Step 3: Create issues</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">You can create Linear issues manually or have OpenCastle create them from a PRD. Use the <code>--tracker linear</code> flag so generated tasks are linked to Linear issue IDs.</p>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">Terminal</div>
              <pre><code>$ npx opencastle pipeline --text "Add user authentication" --tracker linear</code></pre>
            </div>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">Pipeline run (summary):</p>
            <div class="recipe-output">
              <pre><code>  ✓ Step 1/5  Generating PRD...
  ✓ Step 2/5  Validating PRD...
  ✓ Step 3/5  Generating convoy spec...
  ✓ Step 4/5  Validating convoy spec...
  ✓ Step 5/5  Creating Linear issues...

  PRD written to: .opencastle/prd/auth.md
  Convoy spec written to: .opencastle/convoys/auth.convoy.yml
  Created Linear issues: PRJ-210 · PRJ-211 · PRJ-212 · PRJ-213</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> If you prefer manual control, create the epic and child issues in Linear first, then reference their IDs in your convoy spec. OpenCastle will honor pre-existing issues and only create missing ones.</div>
          </section>

          <!-- Step 4 -->
          <section class="recipe-section recipe-step" id="team-step-4">
            <div class="recipe-step__number">4</div>
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Step 4: Assign &amp; partition</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">Map Linear issues to convoy tasks and partition repository ownership so each task runs in an isolated worktree and only modifies allowed paths.</p>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">Example convoy spec</div>
              <pre><code>name: auth-flow
branch: feature/auth-convoy-cvy_9a2
concurrency: 3
tasks:
  - id: api-auth
    tracker_issue: PRJ-210
    agent: backend
    prompt: "Implement authentication API with sessions and JWTs"
    files:
      - src/server/auth/**

  - id: login-form
    tracker_issue: PRJ-211
    agent: frontend
    prompt: "Create login form with client-side validation"
    files:
      - src/ui/auth/**
    depends_on:
      - api-auth

  - id: session-tests
    tracker_issue: PRJ-212
    agent: qa
    prompt: "Add integration tests for auth flow"
    files:
      - tests/integration/auth/**</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> Use <code>depends_on</code> for tasks that require artifacts from prior tasks — this enforces ordering and reduces merge conflicts.</div>
          </section>

          <!-- Step 5 -->
          <section class="recipe-section recipe-step" id="team-step-5">
            <div class="recipe-step__number">5</div>
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Step 5: Execute convoy</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">Start the convoy — agents will run tasks in parallel where possible, open branches, and push changes. Each task writes logs that include the Linear issue ID and will update the issue status as it progresses.</p>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">Terminal</div>
              <pre><code>$ npx opencastle run -f .opencastle/convoys/auth.convoy.yml</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-output">
              <pre><code>  ◎ Convoy started  ·  auth-flow  ·  convoy_id=cvy_9a2

  ✓ [Phase 1]  api-auth         agent=backend  2m 12s  ·  issue=PRJ-210  ·  PRJ-210: In Progress → Done
  ✓ [Phase 2]  login-form       agent=frontend 1m 48s  ·  issue=PRJ-211  ·  PRJ-211: In Progress → Done
  ✓ [Phase 3]  session-tests    agent=qa       0m 56s  ·  issue=PRJ-212  ·  PRJ-212: In Progress → Done

  ✓ Convoy complete  ·  3/3 tasks passed  ·  total 6m 56s
  Branches: feature/auth-convoy-cvy_9a2 (api-auth, login-form, session-tests)</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> Use <code>--retry-failed</code> to selectively re-run failed tasks and <code>--resume</code> after interruptions. Each task persists state so resumes pick up where they left off.</div>
          </section>

          <!-- Step 6 -->
          <section class="recipe-section recipe-step" id="team-step-6">
            <div class="recipe-step__number">6</div>
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Step 6: Review together</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">Open the dashboard to review task logs, diffs and per-task gate results. Confirm each task’s branch and the associated Linear issue before opening a consolidated PR.</p>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">Terminal</div>
              <pre><code>$ npx opencastle run --status</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-output">
              <pre><code>  Task         · Status   · Issue     · Branch
  -----------------------------------------------
  api-auth     · passed   · PRJ-210   · feature/auth-convoy-cvy_9a2
  login-form   · passed   · PRJ-211   · feature/auth-convoy-cvy_9a2
  session-tests· passed   · PRJ-212   · feature/auth-convoy-cvy_9a2</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> Visit the local dashboard at <code>http://localhost:4321</code> to see per-agent logs, gate failures, and the dead-letter queue. Use the dashboard to add reviewers and assign manual checks before merging.</div>
          </section>

          <!-- Step 7 -->
          <section class="recipe-section recipe-step" id="team-step-7">
            <div class="recipe-step__number">7</div>
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Step 7: Ship the PR</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">Push the feature branch and open a pull request. Include all related Linear issue IDs in the PR body — OpenCastle and Linear will use those references to auto-close issues when the PR merges.</p>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">Terminal</div>
              <pre><code>$ git push -u origin feature/auth-convoy-cvy_9a2
$ gh pr create --title "feat: auth flow (convoy cvy_9a2)" --body "Closes: PRJ-210, PRJ-211, PRJ-212\n\nGenerated by OpenCastle convoy cvy_9a2"</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> Use the exact Linear IDs in the PR body (e.g. <code>PRJ-210</code>). When the PR merges, Linear will detect the references and transition issues to <strong>Done</strong> automatically if your workspace rules allow it.</div>
          </section>

          <!-- Tips & Troubleshooting -->
          <section class="recipe-section" id="team-troubleshooting">
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Tips &amp; Troubleshooting</h3>
            <div class="recipe-troubleshooting">
              <div class="recipe-troubleshooting__item">
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__problem">LINEAR_API_KEY not found</p>
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__solution">Make sure you exported the full key (starts with <code>lin_api_</code>) into your shell or <code>.env</code>. After saving the file, restart your terminal or IDE so environment variables are reloaded, then re-run <code>npx opencastle doctor</code> to confirm connectivity.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="recipe-troubleshooting__item">
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__problem">Doctor shows Linear unreachable</p>
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__solution">Check network access and that the key is valid for the workspace you expect. Use the Linear web UI to verify the key permissions; if needed, create a new personal API key and update your <code>.env</code> or CI secret.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="recipe-troubleshooting__item">
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__problem">Task references a non-existent Linear issue</p>
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__solution">Open your convoy spec and confirm the <code>tracker_issue</code> fields contain correct IDs. If the issue was renamed or moved, re-link the task to the correct issue ID and re-run the convoy to update associations.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="recipe-troubleshooting__item">
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__problem">Merge conflicts between tasks</p>
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__solution">Ensure each task has exclusive file globs under <code>files</code> or <code>paths</code> in the convoy spec. If a conflict occurs, resolve it in a short-lived integration branch and update the convoy spec to avoid future overlap.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- What's next -->
          <section class="recipe-section" id="team-whats-next">
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">What's next</h3>
            <ul class="recipe-section__list">
              <li><strong>Automated reviews</strong> — Integrate CI checks and require the dashboard’s gates before merge; see the <a href="/docs/agentic-development">Agentic Development</a> guide.</li>
              <li><strong>Advanced tracing</strong> — Enable richer telemetry and per-task annotations so commits include reviewer notes and trace IDs.</li>
              <li><strong>Custom trackers</strong> — Swap or augment Linear with Jira or GitHub Issues by enabling another tracker plugin in <code>.github/skills/</code>.</li>
              <li><strong>Policy-driven merges</strong> — Create branch protection rules that require convoy gates and manual approvals before PR merge.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

        </article>

        <article class="recipe" id="api-backend">
          <h2 class="recipe__title">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M4 19.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 17H20"/><path d="M6.5 2H20v20H6.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 4 19.5v-15A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 2"/><line x1="8" y1="7" x2="16" y2="7"/><line x1="8" y1="11" x2="13" y2="11"/></svg>
            Build a REST API Backend
