          <!-- Step 1 -->
          <section class="recipe-section recipe-step" id="api-step-1">
            <div class="recipe-step__number">1</div>
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Step 1: Initialize</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">Create a new directory, initialize git and npm, then run the OpenCastle initializer to pick your server framework (Express or Fastify) and baseline plugins.</p>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">Terminal</div>
              <pre><code>$ mkdir task-api
$ cd task-api
$ git init
$ npm init -y
$ npx opencastle init</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-output">
              <pre><code>◎ initializing · creating workspace
· git initialized · ✓
· npm init · ✓
· interactive: choose server framework → Express
· scaffolding plugins · ✓</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> Choose Express for widest community support or Fastify for performance and built-in schema validation support.</div>
          </section>

          <!-- Step 2 -->
          <section class="recipe-section recipe-step" id="api-step-2">
            <div class="recipe-step__number">2</div>
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Step 2: Describe the API</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">Provide a concise pipeline prompt describing the API domain and non-functional requirements — authentication, RBAC, validation, and tests. OpenCastle's pipeline will decompose this into agent tasks.</p>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">Terminal</div>
              <pre><code>$ npx opencastle pipeline --text "Build a REST API for a task management app with users, projects, and tasks. Include JWT authentication, role-based access control, input validation with Zod, and comprehensive test coverage."</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-output">
              <pre><code>◎ pipeline plan · 5 stages · 42 tasks
