· estimated wall time: 18m</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> Keep the prompt focused and include explicit constraints (e.g., "use Zod", "JWT", "SQLite") so generated code matches your stack.</div>
          </section>

          <!-- Step 3 -->
          <section class="recipe-section recipe-step" id="api-step-3">
            <div class="recipe-step__number">3</div>
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Step 3: Review the PRD</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">OpenCastle writes a machine-readable PRD in <code>.opencastle/prd/task-api.md</code>. Review and tweak endpoints, auth rules, and validation before running the convoy.</p>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">File</div>
              <pre><code># .opencastle/prd/task-api.md

## Endpoints
| Method | Path | Auth | Description |
| GET | /api/v1/users | admin, user | list users
| POST | /api/v1/users | admin | create user
| GET | /api/v1/users/:id | admin, user | get user
| PUT | /api/v1/users/:id | admin | update user
| DELETE | /api/v1/users/:id | admin | delete user
| GET | /api/v1/projects | admin, user | list projects
| POST | /api/v1/projects | admin | create project
| GET | /api/v1/projects/:id | admin, user | get project
| PUT | /api/v1/projects/:id | admin | update project
| DELETE | /api/v1/projects/:id | admin | delete project
| GET | /api/v1/tasks | admin, user | list tasks
| POST | /api/v1/tasks | admin, user | create task
| GET | /api/v1/tasks/:id | admin, user | get task
| PUT | /api/v1/tasks/:id | admin, user | update task
| DELETE | /api/v1/tasks/:id | admin, user | delete task

## Auth
- JWT in `Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;`
- Roles: admin, user
- Role checks applied per-route

## Validation
- Users: `email` (email), `password` (min 8)
- Projects: `name` (string, required)
- Tasks: `title` (string, required), `status` (enum: open|in_progress|done), `assigneeId` (uuid)</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> Edit the PRD to reflect custom policies — the convoy will regenerate affected artifacts when you re-run the pipeline.</div>
          </section>

          <!-- Step 4 -->
          <section class="recipe-section recipe-step" id="api-step-4">
            <div class="recipe-step__number">4</div>
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Step 4: Preview the plan</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">Run a dry-run preview to inspect phases and assigned agents before making changes. This is a safe way to confirm the decomposition.</p>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">Terminal</div>
              <pre><code>$ npx opencastle pipeline --dry-run</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-output">
              <pre><code>· preview · dry-run
Phase 1 → setup: install deps, lint rules, DB init
Phase 2 → models: user, project, task models + migrations
Phase 3 → routes: users, projects, tasks endpoints
Phase 4 → middleware: auth, rbac, request validation
Phase 5 → tests: unit + integration + CI config
· no files written · ready to execute</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> Use the dry-run to catch unwanted changes and to map which files will be created or edited.</div>
          </section>

          <!-- Step 5 -->
          <section class="recipe-section recipe-step" id="api-step-5">
            <div class="recipe-step__number">5</div>
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Step 5: Execute</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">Run the convoy to execute the plan. Agents run in isolated worktrees and open PRs for review. Monitor the output for task progress and any retry events.</p>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">Terminal</div>
              <pre><code>$ npx opencastle pipeline --execute</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-output">
              <pre><code>◎ convoy start · 5 stages
[00:00] Stage 1 · setup · agent-setup-01 · initializing environment · ✓
[00:45] Stage 2 · models · agent-models-02 · created models/user.ts, models/project.ts, models/task.ts · ✓
[02:12] Stage 3 · routes · agent-routes-03 · generated routes/users.ts, routes/projects.ts, routes/tasks.ts · ✓
[03:50] Stage 4 · middleware · agent-auth-04 · added jwt middleware · ✓
[05:30] Stage 5 · tests · agent-tests-05 · added integration tests · ✓
[05:45] agent-routes-03 → error: lint failure in routes/tasks.ts · retrying (1/2) · ✓
[06:10] agent-routes-03 · retry succeeded · ✓
· convoy complete · total 6m 20s</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> If an agent fails, the convoy will retry automatically — to resume a partially completed run use <code>npx opencastle pipeline --resume</code>.</div>
          </section>

          <!-- Step 6 -->
          <section class="recipe-section recipe-step" id="api-step-6">
            <div class="recipe-step__number">6</div>
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Step 6: Test the API</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">Run the generated test suite and exercise a sample endpoint locally.</p>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">Terminal</div>
              <pre><code>$ npm test
$ npm start</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-output">
              <pre><code>✓ tests passed · 48 tests · 1.2s
Server listening · http://localhost:3000 · ✓</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">Terminal</div>
              <pre><code>$ curl -s http://localhost:3000/api/v1/tasks | jq</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-output">
              <pre><code>{`{
  "data": [],
  "meta": { "page": 1, "limit": 10, "total": 0 }
}`}</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> Use the OpenCastle dashboard to inspect generated PRs and agent diffs if you want to review changes before merging.</div>
          </section>

          <!-- Step 7 -->
          <section class="recipe-section recipe-step" id="api-step-7">
            <div class="recipe-step__number">7</div>
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Step 7: Review & iterate</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">Open the generated PRs, use your IDE chat to request changes (narrower validation, different error codes, additional endpoints), then push updates and re-run the pipeline for new tasks.</p>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">Terminal</div>
              <pre><code>$ git add .
$ git commit -m "chore: generated API scaffolding"
$ git push origin feature/generated-api
$ gh pr create --title "Generate task API" --body "Generated by OpenCastle convoy"</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> Use iterative PR feedback from reviewers to refine the PRD and re-run targeted pipeline stages rather than full regenerations.</div>
          </section>

          <!-- Tips & Troubleshooting -->
          <section class="recipe-section" id="api-troubleshooting">
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Tips & Troubleshooting</h3>
            <div class="recipe-troubleshooting">
              <div class="recipe-troubleshooting__item">
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__problem">Port 3000 already in use</p>
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__solution">Change the PORT environment variable before starting the server: <code>PORT=4000 npm start</code>.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="recipe-troubleshooting__item">
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__problem">Authentication middleware not applied</p>
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__solution">Check route ordering in the convoy spec and ensure auth middleware is mounted before protected routes in <code>routes/index.ts</code>.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="recipe-troubleshooting__item">
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__problem">Tests failing on CI</p>
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__solution">Ensure CI provides required env vars (JWT secret, DB URL) and run migrations in the CI job before tests.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="recipe-troubleshooting__item">
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__problem">Want to add more endpoints later</p>
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__solution">Create a new PRD at <code>.opencastle/prd/</code> describing the additions and run the pipeline again to generate incremental changes.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- What's next -->
          <section class="recipe-section" id="api-whats-next">
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">What's next</h3>
            <ul class="recipe-section__list">
              <li><strong><a href="/docs/cli-reference">CLI Reference</a></strong> — full command options and flags</li>
              <li><strong><a href="/docs/agentic-development">Agentic Development</a></strong> — guide to working with agent teams and PR workflows</li>
              <li><strong><a href="#team-work">Team Work</a></strong> — recipe for multi-agent collaboration on larger features</li>
              <li><strong><a href="#existing-project">Existing Project</a></strong> — how to onboard OpenCastle into a repo with existing code</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

        </article>

        <article class="recipe" id="existing-project">
          <h2 class="recipe__title">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M4 19.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 17H20"/><path d="M6.5 2H20v20H6.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 4 19.5v-15A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 2"/><line x1="8" y1="7" x2="16" y2="7"/><line x1="8" y1="11" x2="13" y2="11"/></svg>
            Add OpenCastle to an Existing Project
          </h2>

          <!-- Introduction -->
          <section class="recipe-section" id="existing-intro">
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Introduction</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">This recipe shows how to add OpenCastle to a repository that already contains code, tests, CI, and established conventions. OpenCastle is non-destructive — it adds configuration and support files without modifying your existing source. Use <code>npx opencastle detect</code> to scan the repo and automatically identify the tech stack before making changes.</p>
          </section>

          <!-- What you'll set up -->
          <section class="recipe-section" id="existing-what-youll-set-up">
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">What you'll set up</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">A fully configured OpenCastle workspace layered on top of your existing project, with auto-detected plugins, safe-mode pipeline execution, and a first feature built through the convoy. The mockup below represents the detect output scanning an existing repo.</p>

            <div class="recipe-mockup">
              <div class="recipe-mockup__chrome">
                <div class="recipe-mockup__dots"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>
                <div class="recipe-mockup__url">~/projects/my-app</div>
              </div>
              <div class="recipe-mockup__body">
                <pre><code>$ npx opencastle detect
Scanning repository…
Found package.json → Node.js project
Detected framework: Next.js
Detected language: TypeScript
Detected styling: Tailwind CSS
Detected db: PostgreSQL
Detected test runner: vitest
Detected linter: eslint
Generating stack suggestion… ✓
Run `npx opencastle init` to apply config</code></pre>
              </div>
              <div class="recipe-mockup__pages">
                <span class="recipe-mockup__page recipe-mockup__page--active">Detect ·</span>
                <span class="recipe-mockup__page">Init ·</span>
                <span class="recipe-mockup__page">Pipeline ·</span>
                <span class="recipe-mockup__page">Doctor</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <ul class="recipe-section__list">
              <li><strong>Detect</strong> — scan the existing stack and conventions</li>
              <li><strong>Initialize</strong> — add OpenCastle config without touching code</li>
              <li><strong>Plugins</strong> — enable plugins for detected frameworks</li>
              <li><strong>PRD</strong> — create a first PRD for a new feature in the existing codebase</li>
              <li><strong>Safe mode</strong> — run convoy gated on existing tests and lint</li>
              <li><strong>Verify</strong> — review, iterate, and merge through your normal workflow</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <!-- Prerequisites -->
          <section class="recipe-section" id="existing-prerequisites">
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Prerequisites</h3>
            <ul class="recipe-prereq">
              <li>An existing project with git history and at least one commit</li>
              <li>Node.js 20 or later</li>
              <li>An AI coding IDE — VS Code with GitHub Copilot, Cursor, or Claude Code</li>
              <li>An OpenCastle-supported AI model API key</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <!-- Step 1 -->
          <section class="recipe-section recipe-step" id="existing-step-1">
            <div class="recipe-step__number">1</div>
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Step 1: Detect your stack</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">Run detect from the project root. The detector reads common files (package.json, tsconfig.json, config files) to infer frameworks, test runners, linters, and databases.</p>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">Terminal</div>
              <pre><code>$ npx opencastle detect</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-output">
              <pre><code>Scanning repository…
Reading package.json, tsconfig.json, next.config.js
Detected:
  Framework: Next.js
  Language: TypeScript
  Styling: Tailwind CSS
  Database: PostgreSQL
  Test runner: vitest
  Linter: eslint
Suggested stack-config: .opencastle/stack-config.yml
Run `npx opencastle init` to create configuration</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> detect reads package.json, tsconfig, and common config files to identify frameworks, linters, test runners, and databases.</div>
          </section>

          <!-- Step 2 -->
          <section class="recipe-section recipe-step" id="existing-step-2">
            <div class="recipe-step__number">2</div>
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Step 2: Initialize OpenCastle</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">Initialize OpenCastle. Initialization creates configuration directories and baseline instruction files without modifying existing source files.</p>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">Terminal</div>
              <pre><code>$ npx opencastle init</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-output">
              <pre><code>Creating .opencastle/  ✓
Creating .github/instructions/  ✓
Writing default stack-config.yml  ✓
No source files were modified — existing code left intact
Initialization complete</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> OpenCastle never overwrites existing files — if it detects conflicts it skips and reports them.</div>
          </section>

          <!-- Step 3 -->
          <section class="recipe-section recipe-step" id="existing-step-3">
            <div class="recipe-step__number">3</div>
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Step 3: Review detected plugins</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">OpenCastle auto-enables plugins that match your stack. Review and disable any you don't want by setting <code>enabled: false</code>.</p>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">File</div>
              <pre><code># .opencastle/stack-config.yml

framework:
  name: nextjs
  enabled: true
language:
  name: typescript
  enabled: true
styling:
  name: tailwind
  enabled: true
database:
  name: postgresql
  enabled: true
testing:
  name: vitest
  enabled: true
linting:
  name: eslint
  enabled: true</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> Disable plugins you don't want by setting <code>enabled: false</code> in the config.</div>
          </section>

          <!-- Step 4 -->
          <section class="recipe-section recipe-step" id="existing-step-4">
            <div class="recipe-step__number">4</div>
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Step 4: Write a PRD for a new feature</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">Create a PRD under <code>.opencastle/prd/</code> describing a small, scoped feature. Reference existing code paths so agents understand context.</p>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">File</div>
              <pre><code># .opencastle/prd/add-notifications.md

## Title
Add user notifications

## Summary
Implement server-side notifications and a UI inbox for users.

## Scope
- API: /api/notifications (routes in src/pages/api/notifications)
- DB: notifications table (schema in prisma/schema.prisma)
- UI: components in src/components/notifications/

## Acceptance
- Unit tests for API and UI
- Lint & typecheck pass
- Migration added and applied</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> Reference existing code paths (files and folders) so agents can locate relevant code quickly.</div>
          </section>

          <!-- Step 5 -->
          <section class="recipe-section recipe-step" id="existing-step-5">
            <div class="recipe-step__number">5</div>
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Step 5: Run with safe mode</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">Execute the pipeline in safe mode. Safe mode enforces additional validation gates — lint, type-check, and existing tests must pass before changes are proposed.</p>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">Terminal</div>
              <pre><code>$ npx opencastle pipeline --execute --safe-mode</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-output">
              <pre><code>◎ starting pipeline · safe mode enabled
· preflight: eslint · ✓
· preflight: typecheck · ✓
· preflight: vitest · 18 passed, 2 skipped · ✓
◎ convoy start · 3 stages
[00:00] Stage 1 · models · creating notifications table · ✓
[01:30] Stage 2 · routes · generating API endpoints · ✓
[03:00] Stage 3 · components · building notification inbox · ✓
· post-flight: eslint · ✓
· post-flight: typecheck · ✓
· post-flight: vitest · 24 passed, 2 skipped · ✓
· branch: oc/add-notifications · ready for PR</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> Safe mode is recommended for existing projects to prevent regressions.</div>
          </section>

          <!-- Step 6 -->
          <section class="recipe-section recipe-step" id="existing-step-6">
            <div class="recipe-step__number">6</div>
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Step 6: Verify compatibility</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">Run your existing test suite and linter to ensure nothing broke. Use <code>npx opencastle doctor</code> to check workspace health.</p>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">Terminal</div>
              <pre><code>$ npm test
$ npm run lint
$ npx opencastle doctor</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-output">
              <pre><code>✓ vitest · 24 tests passed · 1.8s
✓ eslint · no problems found
◎ opencastle doctor
  · .opencastle config valid · ✓
  · stack-config matches detected stack · ✓
  · no conflicts with existing CI · ✓
  · workspace healthy</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> doctor checks for common configuration issues and reports any conflicts between OpenCastle and existing tooling.</div>
          </section>

          <!-- Step 7 -->
          <section class="recipe-section recipe-step" id="existing-step-7">
            <div class="recipe-step__number">7</div>
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Step 7: Iterate & expand</h3>
            <p class="recipe-section__body">Commit OpenCastle config, create more PRDs, and use OpenCastle progressively for additional features. Start small and increase scope as confidence grows.</p>
            <div class="recipe-code">
              <div class="recipe-code__header">Terminal</div>
              <pre><code>$ git checkout -b chore/opencastle-config
$ git add .opencastle .github/instructions
$ git commit -m "chore: add OpenCastle configuration"
$ git push -u origin chore/opencastle-config</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> Start with small, well-scoped features to build confidence before tackling larger refactors.</div>
          </section>

          <!-- Tips & Troubleshooting -->
          <section class="recipe-section" id="existing-troubleshooting">
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">Tips & Troubleshooting</h3>
            <div class="recipe-troubleshooting">
              <div class="recipe-troubleshooting__item">
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__problem">detect missed a framework</p>
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__solution">Add it manually to <code>.opencastle/stack-config.yml</code> or re-run <code>npx opencastle detect --verbose</code>.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="recipe-troubleshooting__item">
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__problem">init reports file conflicts</p>
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__solution">OpenCastle skips conflicting files — review the skip report and manually merge changes where needed.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="recipe-troubleshooting__item">
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__problem">existing tests fail after convoy</p>
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__solution">Re-run with <code>--safe-mode</code> which gates on your full test suite — inspect failing diffs and revert with git if required.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="recipe-troubleshooting__item">
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__problem">want to use OpenCastle alongside existing CI</p>
                <p class="recipe-troubleshooting__solution">OpenCastle outputs standard git branches and PRs — your existing CI will run as usual on the generated branches.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- What's next -->
          <section class="recipe-section" id="existing-whats-next">
            <h3 class="recipe-section__heading">What's next</h3>
            <ul class="recipe-section__list">
              <li><strong><a href="/docs/cli-reference">CLI Reference</a></strong> — full command options and flags</li>
              <li><strong><a href="/docs/agentic-development">Agentic Development</a></strong> — guide to working with agent teams and PR workflows</li>
              <li><strong><a href="#portfolio">Portfolio</a></strong> — recipe for building a project from scratch</li>
              <li><strong><a href="#api-backend">REST API Backend</a></strong> — recipe for generating a full API</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

        </article>

      </main>
